[4] USA (California)
Date: Sat 18 Apr 2015 [updated]
Source: The Epoch Times [machine trans. edited]
http://www.epochtimes.com/gb/15/4/18/n4414875.htm


The California Health Department recently held a press conference announcing the end of the Disney measles cases. In mid-December last year [2014], triggered by Disney visitors' measles cases, 131 California residents were infected with measles, of which about 40 people were employees of Disney; 30 people were relatives of the families of these people; the rest were infected elsewhere.

Medical staff could never find the original source of infection, but it is believed to be tourists from abroad. Although the United States has announced that measles disappeared decades ago, in recent years, there have still been infections.

A Health Ministry spokesman said that the majority of people infected with measles were not vaccinated, while some people's vaccine history records are not available.

